WEBVTT

00:01.950 --> 00:03.250
[Malory] Now, then, Mr. Crane,

00:03.300 --> 00:07.000
tell us what the Archer
Agency can do for you.

00:07.050 --> 00:08.600
- Well, I...
- Excuse me.

00:08.650 --> 00:10.425
It's the Figgis Agency.

00:10.475 --> 00:12.925
Cyril, please!
Stop interrupting.

00:12.975 --> 00:15.775
Now, Mr. Crane,
how can we help you?

00:15.825 --> 00:19.675
Well, I'm afraid that someone,
or someones,

00:19.725 --> 00:22.600
is trying to sabotage my latest
picture, <i>Deadly Velvet.</i>

00:22.650 --> 00:24.100
[door opens, shoes scuffle]

00:24.150 --> 00:25.775
[chuckling] You mean
besides the critics?

00:25.825 --> 00:28.100
Huh? We're still in production.

00:28.150 --> 00:30.675
It's a joke.
Lighten up, Fritz Lang.

00:30.725 --> 00:31.825
[clears throat]

00:31.875 --> 00:34.150
And what makes you
suspect sabotage?

00:34.200 --> 00:36.275
Well, as Lana can confirm...

00:36.325 --> 00:38.625
Oh-ho-ho, so now it's "Lana"?

00:38.675 --> 00:41.850
Uh, Miss Kane, rather,
who, as you know,

00:41.900 --> 00:43.475
has recently begun working

00:43.525 --> 00:45.950
on the picture as a
technical advisor.

00:46.000 --> 00:47.700
There's already been
three accidents on-set

00:47.750 --> 00:49.325
which were pretty suspicious.

00:49.375 --> 00:51.325
A fire,
a camera crane collapsed...

00:51.375 --> 00:53.200
Narrowly missing
several crew members.

00:53.250 --> 00:55.200
And yesterday, there was
some kind of malfunction

00:55.250 --> 00:56.475
with a stuntman's airbag.

00:56.525 --> 00:59.000
That poor devil
may be paralyzed.

00:59.050 --> 01:01.350
Well,
it certainly sounds suspicious.

01:01.400 --> 01:04.050
But why come to us?
Why not the police?

01:04.099 --> 01:05.474
- I...
- I don't know, Cyril.

01:05.525 --> 01:08.025
Maybe he wanted to be
interrupted every five seconds.

01:08.075 --> 01:09.650
I don't, actually.

01:09.700 --> 01:11.325
And Ellis doesn't want
the police involved.

01:11.375 --> 01:13.150
Oh-ho-ho-ho.
So now it's "Ellis"?

01:13.200 --> 01:15.500
Yes, Archer.
It's Ellis. And Lana.

01:15.550 --> 01:17.150
He and I are on a
first-name basis,

01:17.200 --> 01:19.350
whereas you and
I are on a break!

01:19.400 --> 01:21.225
Yeah, how you holdin' up?

01:21.275 --> 01:23.375
- Pff.
- I'll take that as a "barely."

01:23.425 --> 01:24.900
Take it however you want.

01:24.950 --> 01:26.200
Already did, so...

01:26.250 --> 01:28.375
- Could we...
- Cyril, I swear to God...

01:28.425 --> 01:30.600
Malory!
Ellis wants to hire the agency

01:30.650 --> 01:31.950
to go undercover on the set.

01:32.000 --> 01:33.125
[gasps] Ooh.

01:33.175 --> 01:34.850
You could pose as
technical advisor.

01:34.900 --> 01:36.350
I already am.

01:36.400 --> 01:38.675
- Posing.
- The technical advisor.

01:38.725 --> 01:40.800
And if someone is trying
to sabotage the movie,

01:40.850 --> 01:43.575
- our job is to catch them.
- Discreetly.

01:43.625 --> 01:46.525
If the insurance company
pulls the bond or, God forbid,

01:46.575 --> 01:48.525
my investors back out,
I'll be ruined!

01:48.575 --> 01:51.725
Don't worry, Mr. Crane.
We won't let that happen.

01:51.775 --> 01:53.050
Put your faith in us.

01:53.100 --> 01:55.725
[groans] I'm afraid I must.

01:55.775 --> 01:57.400
We'll see you there
this afternoon.

01:57.450 --> 01:59.575
Ellis,
should we get back to the set?

02:00.825 --> 02:02.550
Meh?
Meh, meh, meh, meh, meh, meh?

02:02.600 --> 02:04.050
[sighs]

02:04.100 --> 02:07.775
- And, uh, how are you holding up?
- Pff.

02:07.825 --> 02:09.574
All right, listen up.

02:09.625 --> 02:13.225
As much as I hate,
hate, hate, hate...

02:13.275 --> 02:15.750
to do this, a movie set is huge,

02:15.800 --> 02:18.550
so we're going to need all of
you to go undercover, so...

02:18.600 --> 02:20.550
- Yay!
- Oh my God, oh my God, oh my God!

02:20.600 --> 02:24.300
[groans] So try to act
like professionals.

02:24.350 --> 02:27.100
Professional whats?
What do we have to do, more work?

02:27.150 --> 02:30.350
Well, I've tried to match the
various production departments

02:30.400 --> 02:33.550
to your skill sets,
such as they are,

02:33.600 --> 02:36.250
so Cyril... accounting.
Get into those books.

02:36.300 --> 02:37.900
Find out who could
benefit from cost overruns

02:37.950 --> 02:39.750
or delays in production.

02:39.800 --> 02:42.575
And that is exactly what I was
going to tell myself to do, so...

02:42.625 --> 02:43.975
Pam... craft services.

02:44.025 --> 02:45.275
Goddamn it.

02:45.325 --> 02:47.475
Wh...
I'm the one who knows macramé.

02:47.525 --> 02:49.950
And you're also
babysitting Carol.

02:50.000 --> 02:52.150
Wh...
Why do I need a babysitter?

02:52.200 --> 02:53.950
Because they've
already had one fire.

02:54.000 --> 02:56.150
[sighs] Then why not
just leave her here?

02:56.200 --> 02:57.625
Because we've
already had one fire.

02:57.675 --> 02:59.300
Now, then, Gillette...

02:59.350 --> 03:00.600
Hair and makeup, hair and makeup,
hair and makeup,

03:00.650 --> 03:01.825
hair and makeup,
hair and makeup!

03:01.875 --> 03:03.000
Finished?

03:03.050 --> 03:04.600
Yes. Grip.

03:04.650 --> 03:05.925
Goddamn it!

03:05.975 --> 03:07.425
Ooh, what about me?
What about me?

03:07.475 --> 03:10.600
Oh,
you just sort of skulk around.

03:10.650 --> 03:12.275
Oh, I will.

03:12.325 --> 03:15.450
And I shall pose as
an executive producer,

03:15.500 --> 03:17.325
which leaves Sterling.

03:17.375 --> 03:20.325
Yeah, it leaves him right here
'cause I'll be damned

03:20.375 --> 03:23.175
if I'm helping Lana's new
pretend boyfriend make a movie.

03:23.225 --> 03:26.125
- Oh, that's too bad.
- Yeah, well...

03:26.175 --> 03:28.025
Krieger,
I suppose you'll just have to be

03:28.075 --> 03:29.800
Veronica Deane's new bodyguard.

03:29.850 --> 03:32.625
- [gasps]
- [car horn blowing]

03:32.675 --> 03:33.850
Let's go, you dumb idiots.

03:33.900 --> 03:35.325
Well, one of you, anyway.

03:35.375 --> 03:37.375
The rest of you,
I guess maybe carpool.

03:37.425 --> 03:39.625
Luigi won't let anybody
ride in the cab.

03:39.675 --> 03:41.875
I mean,
unless you're down for road head.

03:41.925 --> 03:43.650
Shotgun!

03:43.700 --> 03:45.850
<i>♪♪ [theme]</i>

