04:22.750 --> 04:24.400
[Pam] ♪ Lunch, hot lunch! ♪

04:24.450 --> 04:26.425
♪ You get it from
hot lunch Pam ♪

04:26.475 --> 04:28.175
♪ Hot lunch! ♪

04:28.225 --> 04:29.575
[Carol] Okay.
Jesus, why are you in such

04:29.625 --> 04:31.525
an obnoxiously good mood?

04:31.575 --> 04:33.200
Because that crazy dago

04:33.250 --> 04:34.700
let me drive the truck,

04:34.750 --> 04:37.100
so I was the road head-ee.

04:37.150 --> 04:39.100
Yeah. Win for you.

04:39.150 --> 04:42.225
Yep. Just one of the many
perks of having a C.D.L.

04:42.275 --> 04:43.575
What's a C.D.L.?

04:43.625 --> 04:45.600
Commercial driver's license.

04:45.650 --> 04:48.775
And also a [bleep].

04:48.825 --> 04:50.775
Ugh! You are so gross.

04:50.825 --> 04:52.550
[chuckling] That's what he said.

04:52.600 --> 04:54.100
But in Italian.

04:54.150 --> 04:55.550
Who said what in Italian?

04:55.600 --> 04:56.750
Don't ask. You'll gag.

04:56.800 --> 04:59.050
I thought maybe you
dopes had stumbled

04:59.100 --> 05:01.125
onto some sort of
mafia shakedown.

05:01.175 --> 05:02.725
We've been here,
like, four minutes.

05:02.775 --> 05:04.725
Well?
Anything suspicious so far?

05:04.775 --> 05:06.125
Uh, just you?

05:06.175 --> 05:09.100
What, I'm a flamboyant
Hollywood producer.

05:09.150 --> 05:10.400
Not the world's
tiniest drag queen?

05:10.450 --> 05:11.725
What?

05:11.775 --> 05:13.400
I said we'll keep you updated.

05:13.450 --> 05:15.175
Well, you'd better, missy.

05:16.675 --> 05:19.025
Holy shit,
did she just eat a grape?

05:19.075 --> 05:20.325
Must be her cheat day.

05:21.775 --> 05:23.400
[Archer] Man,
it really looks like the '40s.

05:23.450 --> 05:24.900
This is weird, right?

05:24.950 --> 05:27.075
Like the time <i>Star
Trek</i> went to Chicago.

05:27.125 --> 05:30.075
Or Nazi Germany,
for whatever idiot reason.

05:30.125 --> 05:31.250
Archer?

05:31.300 --> 05:33.325
Shapiro?
What are you doing here?

05:33.375 --> 05:34.475
Protecting my client

05:34.525 --> 05:36.625
with my colleagues,
Smith & Wesson.

05:36.675 --> 05:39.175
Oh, really, 'cause I'd
like to meet those guys.

05:39.225 --> 05:40.325
Come on, stop.

05:40.375 --> 05:41.925
First of all,
not a Smith & Wesson.

05:41.975 --> 05:44.000
I know,
but I was going for the whole...

05:44.050 --> 05:46.425
- Second of all, this.
- No, no, no, no, no.

05:46.475 --> 05:47.725
[gun clatters]

05:49.225 --> 05:50.425
Goddamn it.

05:50.475 --> 05:52.425
What the hell, man?
I needed that.

05:52.475 --> 05:53.625
No, you didn't.

05:53.675 --> 05:55.950
Yes, I did.
This set is dangerous.

05:56.000 --> 05:57.800
As dangerous as
you with a firearm?

05:57.850 --> 05:59.275
Are you kid...

05:59.325 --> 06:00.500
Shit's catching on fire.

06:00.550 --> 06:02.000
Shit's falling on people.

06:02.050 --> 06:04.950
People are falling on shit.
Like the ground.

06:05.000 --> 06:07.175
Well, I think it's all just
a big dumb coincidence,

06:07.225 --> 06:10.000
but even if it's not,
don't worry about... [gasps]

06:11.825 --> 06:12.875
Veronica Deane.

06:13.875 --> 06:15.850
Yes? Oh, hello, Alan.

06:15.900 --> 06:17.800
Wait. That's why you're here?

06:17.850 --> 06:19.350
Yeah, Crane hired us.

06:19.400 --> 06:21.525
It's nice to see you again,
Ms. Deane.

06:21.575 --> 06:22.975
I'm sorry. Have we met?

06:23.025 --> 06:24.525
Oh, um, yeah.

06:24.575 --> 06:26.675
I'm Sterling Archer,
private investigator.

06:26.725 --> 06:28.800
You hired me.

06:28.850 --> 06:30.200
Um, and then another time,

06:30.250 --> 06:32.150
I protected you in
a hostage situation,

06:32.200 --> 06:33.550
dressed as a clown.

06:33.600 --> 06:35.550
- Is this not ringing any...
- Alan?

06:35.600 --> 06:38.875
Apparently Ellis hired him to
protect you during the shoot.

06:38.925 --> 06:42.325
Other than my ex-husband's refusal
to let me get on with my life,

06:42.375 --> 06:45.600
the only thing I need protection
from is this clunky dialogue.

06:47.450 --> 06:48.850
Thought I had a joke, but...

06:48.900 --> 06:51.000
Mr... Archer, was it?

06:51.050 --> 06:53.400
Yeah. We actually even kissed.

06:53.450 --> 06:56.025
I'm sorry you've wasted your
time, but I can assure you

06:56.075 --> 06:57.825
I have absolutely no need
for a bodyguard, so...

06:57.875 --> 06:58.875
- [man] Look out!
- [gasps]

07:05.225 --> 07:08.575
[people gasping, yelling]

07:08.625 --> 07:10.375
You were saying?

07:10.425 --> 07:13.175
[sighs]

07:13.225 --> 07:14.800
[chuckling] Yeah, you were.

07:23.550 --> 07:26.225
[man] Move those cans. Now!

07:26.275 --> 07:28.800
Don't you break my cables!
Come on, people!

07:28.850 --> 07:31.000
Move the cables! Careful!

07:31.050 --> 07:32.975
Oh, for God's sakes, what now?

07:33.025 --> 07:35.100
Looks like a runaway forklift.

07:35.150 --> 07:39.100
[groaning] That, and I'm pretty
sure my ribs are shattered.

07:39.150 --> 07:42.000
- Like breadsticks.
- Move those lights, you fools!

07:42.050 --> 07:45.150
Oh,
we're just hemorrhaging money.

07:45.200 --> 07:48.325
- And speaking of hemorrhaging...
- What in the hell happened?

07:48.375 --> 07:50.975
- A forklift.
- And a forkwad.

07:51.025 --> 07:52.775
What's the big idea,
kicking my guts out?

07:52.825 --> 07:55.625
When, just now?
When I saved your life?

07:55.675 --> 07:57.800
- And mine.
- Oh, now...

07:57.850 --> 07:59.625
Oh, please.

07:59.675 --> 08:01.025
What's her problem?

08:01.075 --> 08:02.300
How much time do you have?

08:02.350 --> 08:04.325
[Carol] What is wrong with you?!

08:04.375 --> 08:07.800
[grunting] What's wrong with you,
lady?

08:07.850 --> 08:09.300
You killed it.

08:09.350 --> 08:12.475
It was beautiful,
and you blew it out!

08:12.525 --> 08:15.150
[screams] You maniacs!

08:15.200 --> 08:17.475
You blew it out! Damn you!

08:17.525 --> 08:19.725
Goddamn you all to hell!

08:19.775 --> 08:21.350
What the hell, Tunt?

08:21.400 --> 08:24.150
You leave me to craft all
the service by myself?

08:24.200 --> 08:25.550
I smelled fire.

08:25.600 --> 08:26.700
You mean smoke.

08:26.750 --> 08:28.000
Uh, no.

08:28.050 --> 08:30.025
Oh, I can't believe this.

08:30.075 --> 08:32.650
Yes, it would appear your
"phantom" has struck agai...

08:32.700 --> 08:34.025
Shh-shh-shh-shh...

08:34.075 --> 08:36.500
Back to work, you...
you goldbricks.

08:36.549 --> 08:39.000
All right, you heard the man.
Let's go, let's go, let's go!

08:39.049 --> 08:40.700
[people chattering]

08:40.750 --> 08:42.850
That's exactly the sort of rumor

08:42.900 --> 08:44.350
I don't want you
spreading around.

08:44.400 --> 08:47.050
Maybe this was just an accident.

08:47.100 --> 08:49.200
Nah, somebody definitely
tampered with it.

08:49.250 --> 08:51.250
The brake line's cut,
the steering wheel's tied off,

08:51.300 --> 08:53.250
and the throttle linkage
is jammed wide open.

08:53.300 --> 08:54.575
Yeah, I was gonna say...

08:54.625 --> 08:55.750
linkage jam.

08:55.800 --> 08:57.350
Says the man who pays

08:57.400 --> 08:59.550
to have his Ferrari trucked
around on a flatbed.

08:59.600 --> 09:01.600
And how much is
that costing you?

09:01.650 --> 09:03.525
Actually, not much more
than just driving it,

09:03.575 --> 09:04.900
when you factor in
all the repairs.

09:04.950 --> 09:06.050
Plus no DUIs.

09:06.100 --> 09:07.350
[chuckling] Well, fewer.

09:07.400 --> 09:08.700
And shut up.

09:08.750 --> 09:10.375
You wanna try and make me? Huh?

09:10.425 --> 09:13.200
Now, listen here, you...
you rounder.

09:13.250 --> 09:14.925
You keep a civil tone
here with Ms. Kane,

09:14.975 --> 09:17.050
or I'll throw you off
this set so fast you'll...

09:17.100 --> 09:19.200
you'll pass yourself going.

09:19.250 --> 09:20.875
- Wait, what?
- You'll do nothing of the sort.

09:20.925 --> 09:22.700
Archer is my bodyguard,

09:22.750 --> 09:25.375
and if he goes, you can find
yourself another female lead.

09:25.425 --> 09:27.950
And on the off chance you
plan to shoot anything today,

09:28.000 --> 09:30.275
I'll be in my dressing room!

09:30.325 --> 09:32.425
Archer? Shall we?

09:32.475 --> 09:34.400
[chuckling] Yes,
we probably shall.

09:34.450 --> 09:35.725
Damn it.

09:35.775 --> 09:38.725
Yeah, well Ellis and I will
be in his dressing room, so...

09:38.775 --> 09:40.300
shall we?

09:40.350 --> 09:42.800
Actually, my dear, I need
to go meet with my investors

09:42.850 --> 09:44.925
to cushion the blow about this,

09:44.975 --> 09:47.975
as it were, so... hmm.

09:48.025 --> 09:49.575
So, apparently, you shan't.

09:49.625 --> 09:51.575
Oh, my God, jealous much?

09:51.625 --> 09:54.075
[laughs] Jealous.

09:54.125 --> 09:57.325
It's getting hard to tell the
kettles from the pots around here.

09:57.375 --> 09:59.775
Well, usually,
kettles have whistles.

09:59.825 --> 10:01.075
If that helps.

10:01.125 --> 10:02.325
[sighs]

10:02.375 --> 10:04.450
Hey, Malory,
do you have a minute?

10:04.500 --> 10:07.450
"Malory"?
What happened to "Ms. Archer"?

10:07.500 --> 10:09.925
Well, technically,
they both work for me, so...

10:09.975 --> 10:13.825
So you thought today would be a good
day to try on your big-boy britches

10:13.875 --> 10:15.925
right in the middle
of a mystery?

10:15.975 --> 10:17.100
That's my point.

10:17.150 --> 10:18.775
I think I may have found a clue.

10:18.825 --> 10:20.325
Well, all right, Cyril.

10:20.375 --> 10:24.175
But you'd better just wind
in that neck, Mr. Man.

10:24.225 --> 10:25.800
So, Archer...

10:25.850 --> 10:27.775
would you say women,
on the whole,

10:27.825 --> 10:29.475
found him attractive?

10:29.525 --> 10:31.150
[chuckles] Which hole?

10:31.200 --> 10:32.625
Because yes.

10:32.675 --> 10:34.275
Albeit grudgingly.

10:34.325 --> 10:36.775
[sighs] And sexually,
would you say...

10:36.825 --> 10:39.450
[laughing] Which hole?

10:39.500 --> 10:40.950
[clears throat] Sorry. What?

10:41.000 --> 10:43.825
And would you say he's...
accomplished?

10:43.875 --> 10:45.325
Like, is he good at plowing?

10:45.375 --> 10:46.950
You know he's straight, right?

10:47.000 --> 10:48.975
- I'm...
- Aww, Li'l Baby Elton...

10:49.025 --> 10:50.475
I'm straight.

10:50.525 --> 10:52.375
[gasps] Okay, hypothetically...

10:52.425 --> 10:55.850
No, not... Wait...
Look, I'm in love with Veronica.

10:55.900 --> 10:58.050
I have been since the first
time I laid eyes on her.

10:58.100 --> 10:59.700
I'll never forget that moment.

10:59.750 --> 11:02.650
It felt like I got kicked
in the chest by a mule.

11:02.700 --> 11:04.975
Yeah, you don't forget
a hoof to the tits.

11:05.025 --> 11:06.475
Or shooting your first mule.

11:06.525 --> 11:08.475
Wh...
[sighs] How many have you shot?

11:08.525 --> 11:10.025
Hmm... two.

11:10.075 --> 11:11.975
Anyway,
since she and Crane divorced,

11:12.025 --> 11:13.400
I thought I might have a chance.

11:13.450 --> 11:15.025
[laughs]

11:15.075 --> 11:16.850
But now I'm worried she
might fall for Archer.

11:16.900 --> 11:18.400
If she hasn't already.

11:18.450 --> 11:20.025
Which...

11:20.075 --> 11:21.500
I just need a moment to change

11:21.550 --> 11:23.675
into something more comfortable.

11:23.725 --> 11:25.725
But, please,
do make yourself at home.

11:25.775 --> 11:27.700
<i>Faites comme chez vouz,
</i> as the French say.

11:27.750 --> 11:29.500
Please, take your time.

11:29.550 --> 11:32.000
Oh, and there should be a
bottle of champagne chilling.

11:32.050 --> 11:34.500
- [bottle pops]
- ♪♪ [soft jazz]

11:34.550 --> 11:37.175
So there is.

11:37.225 --> 11:39.425
So you want us to
quit doing our jobs

11:39.475 --> 11:41.025
to help you cockblock Archer?

11:41.075 --> 11:44.375
Well, I... Wait.
Was that sarcastic, or...

11:44.425 --> 11:47.250
- No.
- Then, yeah, I'd love that.

11:47.300 --> 11:48.400
Really?

11:48.450 --> 11:51.100
Enough to shoot a mule?

11:51.150 --> 11:53.100
I mean, not that I think
it'll come to that.

11:53.150 --> 11:54.525
[Malory] You lost me.

11:54.575 --> 11:56.425
[Cyril] Which I think
is the whole point here.

11:56.475 --> 11:58.200
I mean,
in all my years of accounting,

11:58.250 --> 11:59.425
I've never seen
anything like it.

11:59.475 --> 12:02.025
And I've seen some
pretty crazy stuff.

12:02.075 --> 12:04.200
Treating deferred revenue
